  <Subject Subject_ID="300011808">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300011804</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>dung [300011804], feces [300191600], excrement [300191590], animal material by excretions, secretions, and fluids [300191589], animal material by form or function [300191588], animal material [300011793], biological material [300265629], materials by origin [300206573], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A substance that is found on some coasts or islands frequented by sea fowl, composed chiefly of their partially decomposed excrement, rich in phosphate and nitrogenous matter, used extensively as fertilizer. Also refers to excrement of bats.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042061/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sustancia que se encuentra en la costa o islas de algunas regiones frecuentadas por aves marinas, compuesta fundamentalmente de sus excrementos parcialmente descompuestos. Rica en fosfato y materias nitrogenadas, se usa ampliamente como fertilizante. Se refiere también a los excrementos de murciélago.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een substantie die wordt gevonden op bepaalde eilanden en kustgebieden die vaak worden bezocht door zeevogels; bestaat voornamelijk uit hun deels ontbonden excrement. Het is rijk aan fosfaten en stikstofhoudende stoffen en wordt veelvuldig gebruikt als meststof. Wordt ook gebruikt voor excrement van vleermuizen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在常有海鳥棲息的海岸或島嶼所發現的物質，主要成分為海鳥的部分分解排泄物，富含磷酸鹽及含氮物質，廣泛用作肥料。本詞彙也指蝙蝠的排泄物。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Substanz, die auf einigen Küsten und Inseln, die auf ihren Flugrouten von Vögeln frequentiert werden, zu finden ist; es ist im Wesentlichen zersetzter Kot, der reich an Phosphat und stickstoffhaltigen Substanzen ist und als Dünger verwendet wird. Bezieht sich auch auf die Exkremente von Fledermäusen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
